channeldata.summary: Convenience functions for analyzing factorial experiments using ANOVA or mixed models. aov_ez(), aov_car(), and aov_4() allow specification of between, within (i.e., repeated-measures), or mixed (i.e., split-plot)  ANOVAs for data in long format (i.e., one observation per row), automatically aggregating multiple observations per individual and cell  of the design. mixed() fits mixed models using lme4::lmer() and computes  p-values for all fixed effects using either Kenward-Roger or Satterthwaite  approximation for degrees of freedom (LMM only), parametric bootstrap  (LMMs and GLMMs), or likelihood ratio tests (LMMs and GLMMs).  afex_plot() provides a high-level interface for interaction or one-way  plots using ggplot2, combining raw data and model estimates. afex uses  type 3 sums of squares as default (imitating commercial statistical software).
